  • AFL Betting & Odds

    AFL betting is big business as the 18 AFL clubs race towards the Grand Final held each September to decide that years AFL Premiers. AFL odds are open all year with head-to-head markets on every game across the 23-week season, which starts in March and leads to the AFL Finals in September.

     

    Aussie Rules betting on the Premiership Winning team and Brownlow Medal odds on the seasons best and fairest player are also popular. AFL is now loved right around the country after starting out in Victoria. Essendon and Carlton share the record of most VFL / AFL Premiership wins with 16 each. Collingwood meanwhile boast the most AFL Grand Final appearances with 43.

  • How to bet on AFL

    Aussie Rules fans can bet on every round with Ladbrokes AFL Season Pricing markets on all 23 weeks of the regular season. AFL odds fluctuate aggressively throughout the AFL season and the AFL Premiership market is open all year round as the action builds to the AFL Grand Final in September. AFL Line betting is also open on all Australian Rules fixtures.

     

    Ladbrokes punters can access specialty AFL odds on a range of other markets like the seasons Brownlow Medal Winner plus exotic options including the winning margin of a game, first goal kicker and quarter-time score predictions. Theres also the chance for fans to enjoy Live Betting on the AFL.
